 genuine, its differencefrom what actually was to be breaks my heart like the pangs of separation.

No ambition, no honors tainted the fanciful future. The President ofthe Russian Academy advanced toward me to the sound of slow music with awreath on the cushion he held--and had to retreat growling as I shook mygraying head. I saw myself correcting the page proof of a new novel whichwas to change the destiny of Russian literary style as a matter ofcourse--my course (with no self-love, no smugness